            <button class="btn btn-box-tool" data-widget="collapse"><i class="fa fa-minus"></i></button>
            <button class="btn btn-box-tool" data-widget="remove"><i class="fa fa-times"></i></button>
          </div>
        </div><!-- /.box-header -->
        <div class="box-body no-padding">
          <div class="row">
            <div class="col-md-12">
              <div class="pad">Welcome to ~okeanos 位 service pages. Through these pages you can find general information regarding the usage of the 位 service.
              </div>
            </div><!-- /.col -->
          </div><!-- /.row -->
        </div><!-- /.box-body -->
      </div><!--box box-primary-->
    </div><!--col-xs-12-->
  </div><!--row -->

  <div class="row">
    <div class="col-xs-12">
      <div class="box box-info">
        <div class="box-header with-border">
          <h3 class="box-title">Usage Statistics</h3>
          <div class="box-tools pull-right">
            <button class="btn btn-box-tool" data-widget="collapse"><i class="fa fa-minus"></i></button>
            <button class="btn btn-box-tool" data-widget="remove"><i class="fa fa-times"></i></button>
          </div>
        </div><!-- /.box-header -->
        <div class="box-body no-padding">

          <div class="row">
            <div class="col-md-4 col-sm-4">
              <div class="info-box bg-blue">
                <span class="info-box-icon"><i class="fa fa-laptop"></i></span>
                <div class="info-box-content">
                  {{#each model.lambdaInstancesCount as |lambdaInstancesCount|}}
                  <h2 style="padding:4px;line-height:0px;margin-top:12px;">{{lambdaInstancesCount.runningLambdaInstances}} <small><font color="white">lambda instance running</font></small></h2>
                  <h2 style="padding:4px;line-height:0px;margin-top:12px;">{{lambdaInstancesCount.createdLambdaInstances}} <small><font color="white">lambda instance created</font></small></h2>
                  {{/each}}
                </div><!-- /.info-box-content -->
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-4 col-sm-4">
              <div class="info-box bg-orange">
                <span class="info-box-icon"><i class="fa fa-th"></i></span>
                <div class="info-box-content">
                  {{#each model.applicationsCount as |applicationsCount|}}
                  <h2 style="padding:4px;line-height:0px;margin-top:12px;">{{applicationsCount.runningApplications}} <small><font color="white">running applications</font></small></h2>
                  <h2 style="padding:4px;line-height:0px;margin-top:12px;">{{applicationsCount.uploadedApplications}} <small><font color="white">applications uploaded</font></small></h2>
                  {{/each}}
                </div><!-- /.info-box-content -->
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-4 col-sm-4">
              <div class="info-box bg-green">
                <span class="info-box-icon"><i class="fa fa-users"></i></span>
                <div class="info-box-content">
                  {{#each model.usersCount as |usersCount|}}
                  <h2 style="">{{usersCount.count}} <small><font color="white"> subscribed Users</font></small></h2>
                  {{/each}}
                </div><!-- /.info-box-content -->
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

        </div><!-- /.box-body -->
      </div>
    </div>
  </div><!--row-->
  <div class="row">
    <div class="col-xs-12">
      <!-- DIRECT CHAT DANGER -->
      <div class="box box-success ">
        <div class="box-header with-border">
          <h3 class="box-title">Short guide on using the Lambda on Demand service</h3>
        </div><!-- /.box-header -->
        <div class="box-body">
          <div class="row">
            <div class="col-md-12">
              <!-- Conversations are loaded here -->
              <p>The Lambda on Demand service runs on top of GRNET ~okeanos IaaS public cloud. Users of the ~okeanos service can use the Lambda on Demand service in order to instantiate and manage their own Lambda Instances (clusters of VMs utilizing the <a href="http://lambda-architecture.net/">位 (lambda) architectural pattern</a>) with ease and comfort.</p>

              <p>The Lambda on Demand service utilizes Apache Flink on a backend YARN/HDFS installation and Apache Kafka as the data ingestion layer. It also utilizes Apache Flume
              as an Kafka-HDFS connector.</p>

              <p>In order to use the Lambda on Demand (LoD for brevity) service an ~okeanos user will first need to <a href="https://cyclades.okeanos.grnet.gr">spin up a LoD service VM</a> using the publicly available Lambda Service VM image file.<i> We recommend using at least 4 CPUs, 4GB of RAM and 40GB disk size for the LoD service VM.</i></p>

              <p><img src="assets/img/service_vm_image.png" alt="service_vm_image.png" width="500"></p>

              <p>Once the LoD service VM is up and running the user may direct his/her browser to the login page available at the following link:</p>

              <p><b>http://&#123;&#123;hostname&#125;&#125;/</b></p>

              <p><i>Note that one will need to replace the "&#123;&#123;hostname&#125;&#125;" above with the hostname given by the ~okeanos service (usually something of the form snf-XXXXXX.vm.okeanos.grnet.gr) for the LoD service VM.</i></p>

              <h1>Notes and advisories</h1>

              <p>Each LoD Service VM a user instantiates ships with a self signed certificate key pair. We strongly recommend users of the LoD Service VM to replace the self signed key pair with one they may obtain from a Certificate Authority they trust. The files that should be replaced are <code>/etc/apache2/ssl/server.key</code> (private key) and <code>/etc/apache2/ssl/server.crt</code> (public certificate) respectively. Once the change is applied the apache web service should be restarted in order for the changes to take effect:</p>

              <pre>
# service apache2 restart
              </pre>

            </div><!--col-->
          </div><!--row-->
        </div><!--class="box-body"-->
      </div> <!--box-->
    </div><!--col-md-3 -->
  </div>  <!--row-->
</section><!-- /.content -->
